cyclone.name: ROSLYN
cyclone.current_location: about 175 miles south of Zihuatanejo, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to turn WNW then NW and finally north, moving parallel to the southwestern Mexican coast before making landfall along the west-central coast of Mexico.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: west-central Mexico near the Nayarit/Southern Sinaloa coast

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Southwestern and west-central Mexico from Guerrero northward to Sinaloa
weather_observation.wind: No significant tropical-storm-force winds expected at Brownsville.
weather_observation.rainfall: At most, light rain possible early next week from remnant moisture; heavy rainfall not expected.
